SIMPLE: forethink
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forethink
<hw>Fore*think"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
think beforehand; to anticipate in the mind; to prognosticate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The soul of every man⟦br⟧
Prophetically doth <qex>forethink</qex> thy fall.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To contrive (something) beforehend.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forethink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forethink
<hw>Fore*think"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To contrive
beforehand.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forethought</ent>⟦br⟧
